    Ann Louise Rees3 years ago on Google
    5/5
    My partner and I have just returned from a 6 night break at the Adama Resort in Marrakech. Not knowing what to expect we were astounded by this amazing country, its people and culture. The Adama is a large hotel with apartments rather 
    My partner and I have just returned from a 6 night break at the Adama Resort in Marrakech. Not knowing what to expect we were astounded by this amazing country, its people and culture. The Adama is a large hotel with apartments rather than rooms. Its in a peaceful setting only 10 minutes bus ride from the middle of Marrakech. The hotel has 1 indoor bar/restaurant area and an outside dining area. There are 2 pools, a larger one and a smaller one for children. There were plenty of sunbeds around the pool area. There is also a separate outdoor lounging area around a large pond. The hotel never felt overcrowded or noisy we thought this was due to it being a quiet period in February, but we were informed that the hotel was at 80% occupancy. The apartments are very spacious with a bedroom / bathroom/ kitchen / lounge / dinning area / outside space. The breakfast / lunch / dinner times are very generous with plenty of choicethere is something for everyone. The shuttle transfer from the hotel to Marrakech works well, and we made use of this every day. There are large gaps in the transfer times in the afternoon, but it didnt affect us. We didnt have a problem, but the demand for the shuttle could easily exceed the number of seats available at busy times.
    The waiting staff were outstanding. The service we received was exceptional at every level. We were made to feel most welcome, and nothing was too much trouble. There was always a welcome hello and a smile and they made an effort to get to know us, as well as giving advice whilst chatting about our plans. They always checked if wed be dining in the day and evening, and always had a table ready for us. Khalid welcomed us on our arrival on the first day and was always a complete gentleman tending to our needs. Abdel was a great source of information, and gave us some great advice on our planned day trips. Faisal worked relentlessly during busy periods, and was so kind to us. And if you like a Mojito Mounir makes the best cocktails. Thanks to all the fabulous staff!
    We enjoyed a guided tour of the Atlas Mountains on the first day organised through our rep. This is a must when visiting Marrakesh it is an experience not to be missed. You can see just how the Berbers are living and witness some stunning scenery and views. We stopped off at a traditional Berber family, Argan shop and a pottery shop. Nothing was too much trouble and we were always welcomed with a mint tea by the Berbers and learned about their way of life.
    Visiting the souk in the day wasnt half as intimidating as we had imagined. The market stalls were plentiful with everything you could imagine from leather, wicker, to spices and oils. At evening, it is a different matter the square transforms to a crazy bustling crowd. We sat down to try the street food and we were not disappointed.
    We used the 48hr hop on hop off bus it was really reasonably priced and enabled us to see the outskirts of the city. We stopped at the Marjorelle Gardens and Bahia Palace. The entry fees were reasonable and worth a visit.

    About this hotel

    Set on the outskirts of Marrakech in 2.5 acres of century-old olive groves, these refined villas is 9 km from the lively public square Jemaa el-Fnaa and 10 km from Bahia Palace.

    Designed in 4 distinct styles, the modern, airy villas feature free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs. Set around the pool, all have kitchens, living rooms and terraces or patios. Many have mezzanines. Room service is available.

    There's a gourmet restaurant with a terrace, serving a breakfast buffet (fee), and a bar with decor inspired by a desert Berber tent. There's an outdoor pool and a spa with a solarium and hammam. There are indoor and outdoor playgrounds.

    Check-in time: 3:00 PM
    Check-out time: 11:00 AM
